      • NOT_PROCESSED_RECORDS

        public static final SDOCounters NOT_PROCESSED_RECORDS
        Record which could not be processed. Typically a record is considered not-processed when there was an error getting its data or none of the required data could be extracted from it.

      • PROCESSED_RECORDS

        public static final SDOCounters PROCESSED_RECORDS
        Number of records that could be processed. A record is considered to be processed when the required data could be extracted from it such as the record's id or geometry.
